response:
 (Profit is calculated as total earnings minus total cost.)
To calculate the profit, first, find the total earnings. From the $54$ cookies sold at three for $\$1$:
\begin{align*}
\frac{54}{3}\cdot1&=18\cdot1\\
&=\$18
\end{align*}
They also sold $20$ cupcakes for $\$2$ and $35$ cupcakes for $\$1$ respectively:
\begin{align*}
20\cdot 2 + 35 \cdot 1 &=40+35\\
&=75
\end{align*}
Then you add the three together to find the total earnings:
\begin{align*}
18+75 &=\boxed{\textbf{(B) }93}
\end{align*}
Now, since it cost the club $\$15$ to make all the baked goods:
\begin{align*}
93-15 &=\boxed{\textbf{(C) }\$78}
\end{align*}
The profit is $\$78$.

Note that since we do not have any taxes, we can actually get the answer quicker than doing the steps above by subtracting the expenses from each type of baked good from the total before adding/subtracting:
\begin{align*}
&(18 + 75) - 15\\
=&\boxed{\textbf{(C) }\$78}
\end{align*}
